<seg id="97">Comparison of the prices of bridges and tunnels</seg>
<seg id="98">Both auditors examined the bridge prices on the D 8 and A 17 to identify the bridges, which were characterized by particularly high prices, and to compare the bridge prices on the German and Czech side.</seg>
<seg id="99">The investigation was based on mathematical-statistical methods.</seg>
<seg id="100">The tunnels on the D 8 were compared to similar tunnels on the German motorways A 71, A 38 and A 4 because there were no comparable tunnels on the A 17.</seg>
<seg id="101">When preparing this part of the exam, it was important to have a precise definition of the price term.</seg>
<seg id="102">For the comparison of the bridge prices, both auditors agreed on detailed specifications, for example: using the current price paid for the bridge without VAT.</seg>
<seg id="103">(The VAT rates in the Czech Republic and Germany are different and can change.) Not to consider the costs for special foundation measures, to use the rate of the European Central Bank of December 30, 2005 for currency conversion. (29 CZK = 1 €).</seg>
<seg id="104">Bridges of various types (reinforced concrete, prestressed concrete, steel composite and steel) and different sizes are available on both the D 8 and A 17.</seg>
<seg id="105">To ensure the comparability of the tested bridge structures, the bridges were grouped according to their type.</seg>
<seg id="106">The analyzes also took the bridge size into account within these groups.</seg>
<seg id="107">By far the most common were concrete bridges on both sides of the border (20 bridges on the D 8 and 36 bridges on the A 17).</seg>
<seg id="108">The investigation focused on this type of bridge, since the size of the sample allowed the use of mathematical-statistical methods and improved the reliability of the results.</seg>
<seg id="109">The investigation showed that the m² price of the concrete bridges on the D 8 / A 17 depends on the size of the bridge (length, road surface): the larger the bridge, the lower the price per square meter.</seg>
<seg id="110">The correlation between price and size is more pronounced for German bridges than for Czech bridges (see figures below).</seg>
