<seg id="707">After the offers have been checked and evaluated, the award procedure is concluded by awarding the contract or by lifting the procedure.</seg>
<seg id="708">EU law and anti-corruption requirements</seg>
<seg id="709">In EU-wide award procedures, all bidders must be informed in advance of the proposed award decision.</seg>
<seg id="710">The companies have the possibility to check the intended award within 10 days for information electronically or by fax or within 15 days for other means of communication and, if necessary, to initiate a review procedure.</seg>
<seg id="711">A contract may not be concluded before this information period has expired.</seg>
